                            jump to other results
                        </a></div></div><ol class="sense_single" htag="ol"><li class="sense" htag="li" hclass="sense" id="americansocietyforthepreventionofcrueltytoanimals_sng_1"><span class="sensetop" htag="span" hclass="sensetop"><span class="def" hclass="def" htag="span">a US charity that works to protect animals and to prevent them being treated in a cruel way. It also runs centres where people can adopt animals that have no owner, and provides <a class="Ref" href="https://www.oxfordlearnersdictionaries.com/definition/english/veterinary#veterinary_topg_1" title="veterinary definition"><span class="ndv">veterinary</span></a> services and advice on pet care. The charity began in 1866 and is the oldest organization of this type in America. Its main offices are in New York.</span></span>    <div id="ring-links-box">
